report.measDesc: Land use change between 2020 to 2023 for the Southwest Florida Water Management District, according to the Florida Land use Change Classification System
report.evalMethDesc: For this analysis 50% (2230) of the points were taken within polygons where the classification was modified during the change detection process. After the validation assessment of each point was completed, the change points were intersected with the Phase 5 data. The validation classification calls were then compared to the initial LEV 2 change classification. (For further information see report titled FLUCCS_2023_Final_Report_9_30_2024.PDF). An independent accuracy assessment was conducted on level two FLUCCS codes by Pickett and Associates, LLC. The purpose of this assessment was to assign a measure of validity to the product that will allow users to understand the reliability of the data and assist them in determining how they may best use it. The data had an overall rating of 86%, above the goal of 85%. The issues identified by the consultant were edited and corrected April 2025. To receive a copy of this report, contact the Mapping and GIS section, and request the document titled “2023 LU/LC Cover Accuracy Assessment.pdf.”
